The White House held a press briefing at Camp David during the G8 Summit. Deputy National Security Advisors Ben Rhodes and Mike Froman provided an update on the meetings thus far. They discussed the focus on the global economy, the importance of promoting growth and jobs, and the need for fiscal consolidation. They also mentioned discussions on energy and the potential for disruptions in the oil supply. The leaders agreed to support sound and sustainable fiscal consolidation plans, and they affirmed their interest in Greece remaining part of the eurozone. The briefing also touched on the situation in Syria and the need for a political transition.